{"type":"message","id":"18fb67a9","parentId":"33733194","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:17:32.361Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3ecb2ynqxrwe_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 2757\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1346\n[mutation proposed] research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\n[master 26c9650] pulse: 2026-03-24 121716\n 6 files changed, 156 insertions(+), 60 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 121716.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 121716.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 121616.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 121716 - CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0). This suggests frequency-based compression loses signal while CFI-weighted compression should preserve causal structure. The next step is a direct comparison.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quick-trail","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 2757\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1346\n[mutation proposed] research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\n[master 26c9650] pulse: 2026-03-24 121716\n 6 files changed, 156 insertions(+), 60 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 121716.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 121716.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 121616.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 121716 - CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0). This suggests frequency-based compression loses signal while CFI-weighted compression should preserve causal structure. The next step is a direct comparison.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369052359}}
{"type":"message","id":"28ffd831","parentId":"18fb67a9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:17:32.364Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3ecb2ynqxrwe_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 121616\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n\r\nPending work:\r\n1. CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n2. Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n3. Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Design actual compression network\r\n\r\nThe most actionable next step seems to be the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Taking the CFI results from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n2. Implementing a weighting scheme that prioritizes high-CFI tokens\r\n3. Comparing next-pulse prediction quality vs the frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what's ready to work with. I should look at the CFI_RESULTS.md to understand the data structure, then design the experiment.\r\n\r\nA concrete action: Create a new experiment file that defines the CFI-weighted compression experiment methodology, or implement a simple Python script that performs the compression comparison.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete, actionable experiment design file.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0) and only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). This suggests a CFI-weighted compression could significantly improve next-pulse prediction by filtering out noise while preserving research trajectory.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a new experiment file defining the CFI-weighted compression methodology and implementation plan, building directly on the CFI_RESULTS.md findings.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted token retention will outperform frequency-based compression for next-pulse prediction by filtering metaprogramming noise while preserving causal research anchors.\r\n\r\n## Background\r\nFrom `CFI_RESULTS.md`:\r\n- 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)  \r\n- Mean CFI = 0.181 (frequency compression is mostly signal loss)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Compression Strategies to Compare\r\n\r\n| Strategy | Selection Criterion | Expected Outcome |\r\n|----------|---------------------|------------------|\r\n| **Baseline** | Top-k by frequency | Retains format tokens, noise |\r\n| **CFI-Weighted** | Top-k by CFI × frequency | Prioritizes causal + frequent |\r\n| **CFI-Filtered** | CFI >= threshold, then frequency | Removes noise, retains anchors |\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Prediction Quality\r\n1. **Token overlap**: % of predicted tokens appearing in actual next pulse\r\n2. **Research continuity**: % of high-CFI tokens (from prior pulse) retained\r\n3. **Noise rejection**: % of CFI=0 tokens excluded\r\n\r\n### Implementation Steps\r\n\r\n1. **Parse pulse history** (pulse_*.md files)\r\n2. **Compute token frequencies** across last N pulses\r\n3. **Compute CFI scores** for each invariant token\r\n4. **Apply each compression strategy** to generate \"compressed state\"\r\n5. **Compare against actual next pulse** to score prediction quality\r\n\r\n### Data Sources\r\n- Pulse history: `pulse_*.md` files in root\r\n- CFI scores: Computed from frequency invariance analysis\r\n- Ground truth: Next actual pulse file\r\n\r\n## Next Action\r\nImplement `experiments/cfi_compression_test.py` to execute the comparison.\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:16:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774369052361}}
